# LaTeX Expert

Generate publication-quality LaTeX documents for scientific and technical writing.

## Core Rules \(MANDATORY\)

### 1. Verify LaTeX Installation

Before compiling, check for a TeX distribution:

```bash
pdflatex --version 2>/dev/null || xelatex --version 2>/dev/null || lualatex --version 2>/dev/null
```

IF no LaTeX found:
THEN instruct user to install MiKTeX \(Windows\) or TeX Live:
```bash
# Windows \(via winget\)
winget install MiKTeX.MiKTeX

# Or download from https://miktex.org/download
```

### 2. Output Files Only

- Write `.tex` source files to the user-specified location \(default: `~/Desktop/`\)
- Compile to PDF only when user requests it
- Never delete source files after compilation

### 3. Clean LaTeX

- Use standard packages only \(no exotic dependencies\)
- Prefer `\\usepackage{amsmath, amssymb, amsthm}` for math
- Use `hyperref` last in preamble \(avoids conflicts\)
- Use `biblatex` with `biber` backend for references

## Document Types

### Scientific Paper \(IEEE/ACM style\)

```latex
\\documentclass[conference]{IEEEtran}
% or \\documentclass{acmart} for ACM

\\usepackage{amsmath, amssymb}
\\usepackage{graphicx}
\\usepackage{booktabs}
\\usepackage[colorlinks=true]{hyperref}

\\title{Your Title Here}
\\author{Author Name \\\\ Organization \\\\ email@example.com}

\\begin{document}
\\maketitle
\\begin{abstract}
...
\\end{abstract}

\\section{Introduction}
...

\\bibliographystyle{IEEEtran}
\\bibliography{references}
\\end{document}
```

### Technical Report

```latex
\\documentclass[11pt,a4paper]{article}

\\usepackage[margin=1in]{geometry}
\\usepackage{amsmath, amssymb}
\\usepackage{graphicx}
\\usepackage{booktabs}
\\usepackage{listings}
\\usepackage{xcolor}
\\usepackage[colorlinks=true]{hyperref}

\\lstset{
  basicstyle=\\ttfamily\\small,
  keywordstyle=\\color{blue},
  commentstyle=\\color{gray},
  stringstyle=\\color{red},
  breaklines=true,
  frame=single
}

\\title{Technical Report Title}
\\author{Author Name}
\\date{\\today}

\\begin{document}
\\maketitle
\\tableofcontents
\\newpage

\\section{Executive Summary}
...

\\section{Technical Details}
...

\\end{document}
```

### Thesis / Dissertation

```latex
\\documentclass[12pt,oneside]{book}

\\usepackage[margin=1.25in]{geometry}
\\usepackage{setspace}
\\usepackage{amsmath, amssymb, amsthm}
\\usepackage{graphicx}
\\usepackage{booktabs}
\\usepackage[backend=biber,style=numeric]{biblatex}
\\usepackage[colorlinks=true]{hyperref}

\\addbibresource{references.bib}
\\doublespacing

\\title{Thesis Title}
\\author{Student Name}
\\date{Month Year}

\\begin{document}
\\frontmatter
\\maketitle

\\chapter*{Abstract}
...

\\tableofcontents
\\listoffigures
\\listoftables

\\mainmatter
\\chapter{Introduction}
...

\\backmatter
\\printbibliography
\\end{document}
```

### Formal Letter / Memo

```latex
\\documentclass[11pt]{letter}

\\usepackage[margin=1in]{geometry}
\\usepackage[colorlinks=true]{hyperref}

\\signature{Your Name \\\\ Title \\\\ Organization}
\\address{Organization \\\\ Address Line 1 \\\\ City, State ZIP}

\\begin{document}
\\begin{letter}{Recipient \\\\ Their Organization \\\\ Address}

\\opening{Dear Recipient,}

Body text here.

\\closing{Sincerely,}

\\end{letter}
\\end{document}
```

### Presentation \(Beamer\)

```latex
\\documentclass{beamer}

\\usetheme{Madrid}
\\usecolortheme{default}

\\usepackage{amsmath}
\\usepackage{graphicx}
\\usepackage{booktabs}

\\title{Presentation Title}
\\subtitle{Subtitle}
\\author{Author Name}
\\institute{Organization}
\\date{\\today}

\\begin{document}
\\frame{\\titlepage}

\\begin{frame}{Outline}
\\tableofcontents
\\end{frame}

\\section{Introduction}
\\begin{frame}{First Slide}
\\begin{itemize}
  \\item Point one
  \\item Point two
  \\item Point three
\\end{itemize}
\\end{frame}

\\end{document}
```

## Common Packages Reference

| Package | Purpose | Usage |
|---------|---------|-------|
| `amsmath` | Advanced math | Equations, align environments |
| `amssymb` | Math symbols | Extended symbol set |
| `amsthm` | Theorem environments | theorem, lemma, proof |
| `graphicx` | Images | `\\includegraphics` |
| `booktabs` | Professional tables | `\\toprule, \\midrule, \\bottomrule` |
| `listings` | Code listings | Syntax-highlighted code |
| `algorithm2e` | Algorithms | Pseudocode |
| `tikz` | Diagrams | See `hdoc:tikz-flowchart` skill |
| `geometry` | Page margins | `\\usepackage[margin=1in]{geometry}` |
| `hyperref` | Links | Clickable references \(load LAST\) |
| `biblatex` | Bibliography | Modern citation management |
| `siunitx` | Units | SI units formatting |
| `cleveref` | Smart refs | `\\cref{fig:example}` |
| `subcaption` | Subfigures | Multiple figures side-by-side |
| `enumitem` | Custom lists | Fine-tuned list formatting |
| `fancyhdr` | Headers/footers | Custom page headers |
| `xcolor` | Colors | Named and custom colors |
| `tcolorbox` | Colored boxes | Callouts, highlighted blocks |

## Math Examples

### Equations

```latex
% Inline math
The formula $E = mc^2$ describes...

% Display math
\\begin{equation}
  \\nabla \\cdot \\mathbf{E} = \\frac{\\rho}{\\epsilon_0}
  \\label{eq:gauss}
\\end{equation}

% Aligned equations
\\begin{align}
  f\(x\) &= x^2 + 2x + 1 \\\\
       &= \(x + 1\)^2
\\end{align}

% Matrix
\\begin{equation}
  A = \\begin{bmatrix}
    a_{11} & a_{12} \\\\
    a_{21} & a_{22}
  \\end{bmatrix}
\\end{equation}
```

### Theorems

```latex
\\newtheorem{theorem}{Theorem}[section]
\\newtheorem{lemma}[theorem]{Lemma}
\\newtheorem{definition}{Definition}[section]

\\begin{theorem}[Fundamental Theorem]
  For every $\\epsilon > 0$, there exists...
\\end{theorem}

\\begin{proof}
  By induction on $n$...
\\end{proof}
```

## Tables

```latex
\\begin{table}[htbp]
  \\centering
