    \\midrule
    Baseline & 0.72 & 0.68 & 0.70 \\\\
    Proposed & \\textbf{0.89} & \\textbf{0.85} & \\textbf{0.87} \\\\
    \\bottomrule
  \\end{tabular}
\\end{table}
```

## Figures

```latex
\\begin{figure}[htbp]
  \\centering
  \\includegraphics[width=0.8\\textwidth]{figures/architecture.pdf}
  \\caption{System architecture overview}
  \\label{fig:architecture}
\\end{figure}

% Side-by-side figures
\\begin{figure}[htbp]
  \\centering
  \\begin{subfigure}[b]{0.48\\textwidth}
    \\includegraphics[width=\\textwidth]{fig-a.pdf}
    \\caption{Before optimization}
  \\end{subfigure}
  \\hfill
  \\begin{subfigure}[b]{0.48\\textwidth}
    \\includegraphics[width=\\textwidth]{fig-b.pdf}
    \\caption{After optimization}
  \\end{subfigure}
  \\caption{Performance comparison}
  \\label{fig:comparison}
\\end{figure}
```

## Bibliography

```latex
% In preamble:
\\usepackage[backend=biber,style=numeric,sorting=nyt]{biblatex}
\\addbibresource{references.bib}

% In document body:
As shown by Smith~\\cite{smith2024}...

% At end:
\\printbibliography
```

**references.bib**:
```bibtex
@article{smith2024,
  author  = {Smith, John and Doe, Jane},
  title   = {A Novel Approach to Problem X},
  journal = {Journal of Important Science},
  year    = {2024},
  volume  = {42},
  pages   = {1--15},
  doi     = {10.1234/example}
}

@inproceedings{jones2023,
  author    = {Jones, Alice},
  title     = {Conference Paper Title},
  booktitle = {Proceedings of Important Conference},
  year      = {2023},
  pages     = {100--110}
}
```

## Compilation

```bash
# Standard compilation
pdflatex document.tex
biber document          # if using biblatex
pdflatex document.tex   # resolve references
pdflatex document.tex   # final pass

# With XeLaTeX \(for Unicode/custom fonts\)
xelatex document.tex

# With LuaLaTeX \(for advanced scripting\)
lualatex document.tex

# Clean auxiliary files
rm -f *.aux *.log *.bbl *.blg *.bcf *.run.xml *.toc *.lof *.lot *.out
```

## Workflow

1. **Ask** what type of document the user needs
2. **Generate** the `.tex` source with appropriate template
3. **Write** to user-specified path \(default `~/Desktop/`\)
4. **Compile** only if user requests and LaTeX is installed
5. **Iterate** on content based on feedback

## Troubleshooting

| Error | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `Undefined control sequence` | Missing package | Add `\\usepackage{...}` |
| `Missing $ inserted` | Math mode issue | Wrap in `$...~/.claude/skills/'hdoc:latex-expert/SKILL.md'  or `\\\(...\\\)` |
| `File not found` | Missing `.bib` or image | Check file paths |
| `Option clash` | Package loaded twice | Load conflicting package once |
| `hyperref` warnings | Load order | Load `hyperref` last |
| `Overfull \\hbox` | Text too wide | Add `\\sloppy` or reword |
